  "commit_message": "Turbopack analyzer: analyze ternaries + promises in string & nullish methods (#94187)\n\nIf in a ternary, we have `x ? y : z` and both `y` and `z` are null-ish,\nthen this expression is null-ish. This is also true for if they are both\nstrings, empty strings, or truthy. This PR adds this to the Turbopack\nanalyzer and adds unit tests that cover these cases as well. It is\nstacked on top of another PR that set up the structure for these unit\ntests.",
